commentTextItems.html: outside the off, short, punched
away past covers in fine style, that seals an Australian win by 9
wickets

commentPostTextItems.html: End of a comprehensive win by Australia . The Aussies have now
registered two fantastic wins in this World Cup
India on the other hand have had a terrible run
The Man of the Match has got to be Jason Gillespie who bowled a
fiery spell earlier on scalping 3 wickets for just 13 runs
The Indian batsmen all threw away their wickets barring Tendulkar
who played one or two pretty shots
All in all though a clinical performance from the Aussies. The
Indians were never in the game after the Australian fast bowlers
destroyed the Indian top order
We're just waiting for the official announcement of the Man of the
Match award. We'll bring that news to you shortly
In the meantime remember that the Kenya v Canada game is also on.
You can check the scores to that game on www.cricinfo.com
News is just filtering that Jason Gillespie has been named the Man
of the Match. Rightfully so!
On that note CricInfo brings the curtain down on the India v
Australia game at Centurion. Do log on to the website for all the
complete coverage!
We enjoyed bringing this game to you, we hope you enjoyed our
coverage. Please do send all feedback to comms@cricinfo.com!
